In React, the "state" is a JavaScript object that represents the dynamic behavior of a 
component. We can use the state to store data in our components that can change upon 
rendering.

The state is usually initialized in the constructor method of a component and then 
updated in the lifecycle methods of the component. After updating the state, the 
components UI is automatically refreshed, which reflects the updated state to the user.

Using state with React components, we can make our UI responsive, track user input, and 
dynamically manipulate our components.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"React" me state ek JavaScript object hota hai, jo component ke dynamic behavior ko 
represent karta hai. State ki help se, hum apne components ko data store karne ke liye 
use kar sakte hai jo component ke render hone par change ho sakta hai.

State aksar component ke constructor method mein initialize kiya jata hai, aur phir 
component ke lifecycle methods mein update kiya ja sakta hai. State ko update karne ke 
baad, component ka UI automaticaly refresh hota hai, jisse updated state ka reflection 
user ko dikhai deta hai.

React ke components ke saath state ka use karne se, aap apne UI ko responsive bana sakte 
hai, user input ko track kar sakte hai aur apne component ko dinamic tarike se upyog kar 
sakte hai.